{"key":"processedPost-19451896","value":{"id":19451896,"first":19448610,"last":19457859,"when":1390319069,"utime":"01/21/14 05:44 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>maxpad84 said:</strong><br />I got this method of of Damian's 50/50 tech done it a few times with good results. In the tech it calls for a thin layer of berm and coir on top of the mix, I assumed it was a casing due to the nature of it. So after this tech is fully colonized a casing would be a good to apply?</blockquote><br />The tek calls for a thin layer of verm/coir over the top after spawning for the purpose of covering all the exposed grains.&nbsp; It's not a casing layer and it colonizes at the same time as the substrate, which it's a part of.&nbsp; If one leaves grains exposed, they dry out which causes the mycelium to die-back.&nbsp; Green molds then move into the available habitat, ruining the project.<br />Your thread title should have read 'ideal amount of colonization for <i>substrate</i>'.<br />RR","title":"Re: What is the ideal amount of colonization for casing?"}}